<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-01-24T14:00:00-05:00" n="696" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d696">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 300.115/11342</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-01-24T19:00:00+00:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">January 24, 1917, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 10.45 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>5537. Department’s 4117, December 2, 3 p. m., my 5290, December 7, 4
                                p. m., and Department’s 4250, January 5, 4 p. m., <hi rend="italic">re</hi> modification of instructions. Foreign Office informs me
                                it has “decided to make a special concession in regard to the two
                                consignments.” British Consul, Rotterdam, authorized to issue on
                                application permits for shipment 10,000 bags to
                                    <persName>DeRekowski</persName> and 10,215 bags Michigan Sugar
                                Company.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_PWH1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Page</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>